The occasions are so important young men return from abroad to the crisp mountain snows, just for the winter weddings.

People in Ribnovo identify themselves more by their religion, as Muslims, than by their ethnicity or nationality, and the wedding ceremony is an expression of their piety.

The village has 10 clerics and two mosques for 3,500 inhabitants.

