'It is very 
likely that it is an invented tradition. It's their way to express who 
they are,' said Margarita Karamihova, an associate professor at the 
Ethnography Institute of the Bulgarian Academy of Science.

Experts
 say Pomaks had identity problems and faced more challenges than the 
majority of Muslims in Bulgaria, who are ethnic Turks.

'In
 the 1960s they would ban Islamic music at weddings, then they would not
